
How to Create a Dockerfile :

Dockerfile is a text file that contains instructions to build a Docker Image.

touch Dockerfile
vi Dockerfile

--> basic docker file

FROM nginx:latest
COPY . /usr/share/nginx/html
EXPOSE 80
CMD ["nginx", "-g", "daemon off;"]

Build image:
docker build -t mywebsite:v1 .
Run:
docker run -d -p 80:80 mywebsite:v1

Dockerfile Common Syntax (Most Important)

1. FROM
Defines base image.

FROM ubuntu:22.04

Examples:

Ubuntu
NGINX
Node.js
OpenJDK

✅ Usually first line.

2. WORKDIR
Sets working directory inside container.

WORKDIR /app

Equivalent to cd /app.

3. COPY
Copies files from host to image.

COPY . .
COPY app.jar /app/

4. ADD
Like COPY, but can extract archives / URL support.

ADD app.tar.gz /app/

Usually prefer COPY.

5. RUN
Executes commands during image build.

RUN apt update && apt install -y curl
RUN npm install
Used for package installation.

6. ENV
Set environment variables.

ENV APP_ENV=production
ENV PORT=8080

7. EXPOSE
Documents port used by container.

EXPOSE 80
EXPOSE 8080

8. CMD
Default command when container starts.

CMD ["nginx", "-g", "daemon off;"]

Only one CMD normally.

9. ENTRYPOINT
Main fixed startup command.

ENTRYPOINT ["java","-jar","app.jar"]

Often combined with CMD.

10. USER
Run as specific user.

USER appuser

Security best practice.

11. LABEL
Metadata.

LABEL maintainer="Aditya"

Example: Java Spring Boot Dockerfile
FROM openjdk:17
WORKDIR /app
COPY target/app.jar app.jar
EXPOSE 8080
CMD ["java","-jar","app.jar"]

Build:

docker build -t springboot:v1 .

Run:

docker run -d -p 8080:8080 springboot:v1


Example: Node.js Dockerfile
FROM node:20
WORKDIR /app
COPY package*.json ./
RUN npm install
COPY . .
EXPOSE 3000
CMD ["npm","start"]


Example: Python Dockerfile

FROM python:3.12
WORKDIR /app
COPY requirements.txt .
RUN pip install -r requirements.txt
COPY . .
CMD ["python","app.py"]
